nodes.text: The Dryorkeen Cluster was a galactic location where a famine occurred during the Imperial Era. Yrica Quell, a TIE fighter pilot in the Galactic Empire's 204th Imperial Fighter Wing, believed that the Empire failed to help with the famine. She voiced this opinion to Major Soran Keize when expressing her distaste in what the Empire's inefficiency and excessive blaming of the Rebel Alliance in the process.
The Dryorkeen Cluster was first mentioned in the 2019 novel Alphabet Squadron, written by Alexander Freed.
